  "target_response": {
    "text": "Your data points at timing, not quantity. Last night you slept 7.3 h with an efficiency of 92% — once you're in bed, sleep itself works fine. The weak spot is your consistency score of 58%, which means your bed and wake times are drifting substantially from night to night. Irregular timing often lines up with exactly your complaint — enough hours but groggy mornings — because the body's clock keeps re-anchoring. These are estimated scores, so don't chase the numbers themselves; chase the habit they're flagging. One behavior to test for two weeks: fix your wake time to the same slot seven days a week, weekends included, and let bedtime settle naturally. If the grogginess is clock-driven, mornings tend to improve within the first two weeks, and the consistency score will confirm the shift.",
